# tkv2 - button size: compact/regular/large button sizing (std-ui-button-size)

Slice `std-ui-button-size` (`specs/std-ui-button-size.md`): the four button
constructors (`signalButton`, `actionButton`, `signalLabelButton`,
`signalActionButton`) accept a new trailing `size` param (after `variant`)
that `lower.ssc` resolves to a font-size + padding pair via
`_buttonFontSize`/`_buttonPadding`. `View` is opaque to `.ssc` (see
`specs/std-ui-select.md` "Why no new extern def"), so — mirroring
`tests/conformance/tkv2-button-variant.ssc`'s own TkNode-field-assertion
style — this conformance test asserts the `size` field threads from each
constructor to its node unchanged, and that `lower()` does not throw for
every accepted size plus an unrecognized string, on both lanes. The actual
rendered CSS font-size/padding swap (that the resolved values genuinely
differ per size) is verified at the Scala level; see
`specs/std-ui-button-size.md` § Results.

[signal, setSignal](std/ui/primitives.ssc)
[signalButton, actionButton, signalLabelButton, signalActionButton](std/ui/input.ssc)
[SignalButtonNode, ActionButtonNode, SignalLabelButtonNode, SignalActionButtonNode](std/ui/nodes.ssc)
[lower](std/ui/lower.ssc)
[defaultTheme](std/ui/theme.ssc)

```scalascript
val sig      = signal("tkv2ButtonSizeSig", "")
val labelSig = signal("tkv2ButtonSizeLabel", "Go")
val handler  = setSignal(sig, "clicked")

// No `variant`/`size` argument at all — stays the pre-existing default
// ("primary"/"md"), backward compatible with every call site that predates
// this slice.
val defaultBtn = signalButton(sig, "x", "Default")
defaultBtn match
  case SignalButtonNode(_, _, label, _, variant, size) => println(label + ":" + variant + ":" + size)
  case _                                                => println("?")
val defaultView = lower(defaultBtn, defaultTheme)
println("default-built")

// Each accepted size threads through actionButton's constructor to the
// node unchanged, and lowers without throwing.
val bSm = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "primary", "sm")
bSm match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, _, size) => println(label + ":" + size)
  case _                                      => println("?")
val vSm = lower(bSm, defaultTheme)

val bMd = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "primary", "md")
bMd match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, _, size) => println(label + ":" + size)
  case _                                      => println("?")
val vMd = lower(bMd, defaultTheme)

val bLg = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "primary", "lg")
bLg match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, _, size) => println(label + ":" + size)
  case _                                      => println("?")
val vLg = lower(bLg, defaultTheme)

// An unrecognized size string threads through unchanged (the fallback to
// md happens in lower.ssc's _buttonFontSize/_buttonPadding, not at
// construction) and must not crash either the node build or the lowering.
val bBogus = actionButton(handler, "Act", false, "primary", "bogus")
bBogus match
  case ActionButtonNode(_, label, _, _, size) => println(label + ":" + size)
  case _                                      => println("?")
val vBogus = lower(bBogus, defaultTheme)
println("action-sizes-built")

// signalLabelButton / signalActionButton accept and thread `size` the
// same way, independent of `variant`.
val lb = signalLabelButton(sig, "x", labelSig, false, "danger", "sm")
lb match
  case SignalLabelButtonNode(_, _, _, _, variant, size) => println("label-btn:" + variant + ":" + size)
  case _                                                 => println("?")
val vLb = lower(lb, defaultTheme)

val sab = signalActionButton(handler, labelSig, false, "success", "lg")
sab match
  case SignalActionButtonNode(_, _, _, variant, size) => println("action-sig-btn:" + variant + ":" + size)
  case _                                               => println("?")
val vSab = lower(sab, defaultTheme)

println("button-size-built")
```
